   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From your Package Savings Program, go to Qualifications and Benefits tab.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Add products to your package. By, default, the package type is Primary. Refer to <xref href="../adding-products_102432695_102432695/102432695.dita"
                     format="dita"
                     class="- topic/xref ">Adding Products</xref> for more details.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click Save.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To add a product as secondary, under the Products in Bundle tab, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add Secondary Product</uicontrol> from the more menu.  A copy of the primary package is created with Package Type as Secondary. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="603"
                         href="../attachments/102432721/102432726.png"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Enter the unit price.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The bundle price is auto-calculated to reflect all the changes.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click Save.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">You can also add a product as a secondary product directly from the Product Catalog. When adding a product from the product catalog, set Package Type as Secondary Package and save.</p>
